The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Good Morning
      Hello It's Friday , July 23 , 2010                    
	Petrol strike    Most petrol pumps in the city will remain closed on Friday as the West Bengal Petroleum Dealers Association has called a shutdown to protest irrational policies of oil companies. Six outlets will remain open to vehicles on emergency service, such as ambulances and those of police, fire services and media. They are: 
  Teen Murti near Kala Mandir      IOC pump in Patuli
    IOC pump on Bypass-Kasba connector      BP pump in Salt Lake Sector V
      IOC pump on Kona Expressway       BP pump in Uluberia				 																																	  The shutdown will continue from 6am to 9pm.      
	Workshop    Filmi Chashma, a workshop to sensitise young filmmakers about making of childrens films, at Chitrabani, 10am to 6pm.    
	Art watch    Summer Show 2010, an art exhibition at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.    Monsoon Mix at Studio21, 11am to 7pm.    Bengal Painters 10, exhibition of painting and sculpture, at Academy of Fine Arts (North gallery), 3pm-8pm.    War and Forgiveness, a photography exhibition, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6.30pm to 8pm.    A painting exhibition at Weavers Studio Centre for Arts, 10am-7pm.    Writing Visuals, an exhibition, at Harrington Mansions, noon-8pm.    Art for Life, an exhibition of paintings, at Academy of Fine Arts (New south-A Gallery) 3pm to 8pm.    This Is Unreal, a contemporary art exhibition, at Experimenter, 2/1 Hindustan Road, 6pm to 8pm.                                                                                                                                               
